id: pm-7o0s
title: "Sentry PM-CLI-1T: pm stats should tolerate disappearing history streams"
description: "Sentry gate found PM-CLI-1T: pm stats can emit raw ENOENT when a history .jsonl stream disappears between directory enumeration and read during active tracker writes."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[6]: "area:history","area:stats","area:storage",race-condition,release-blocker,sentry
created_at: "2026-06-25T04:55:08.065Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-25T05:29:21.337Z"
author: codex-pm-ecosystem-audit-20260625
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: History-stream ENOENT between readdir and readFile is reproduced or simulated; pm stats skips disappearing streams without sending raw ENOENT to Sentry; non-ENOENT history read failures still surface; focused tests cover the race; Sentry gate passes after PM-CLI-1T is resolved or no longer blocking.
parent: pm-34gb
repro_steps: Run pm stats while another pm process creates/removes history stream files; Sentry PM-CLI-1T shows ENOENT from readHistoryStreamContents during pm stats.
resolution: Handled disappearing history-stream ENOENT as a benign concurrent-write race in pm stats while preserving non-ENOENT read failures; resolved Sentry PM-CLI-1T after the fix and verified the Sentry/telemetry release gate.
expected_result: pm stats tolerates concurrent history stream disappearance as a benign race and still reports aggregate storage metrics.
actual_result: Regression tests pass; pm stats --storage --json passes; Sentry/telemetry gate passes with sentry critical=0/high=0 and telemetry required-mode ok.
